5. API Integration Pattern
API Client Setup
typescript
// services/apiClient.ts
class ApiClient {
  private client: AxiosInstance;

  constructor() {
    this.client = axios.create({
      baseURL: import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL,
      timeout: 30000,
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
    });

    // Request interceptor: Add auth token
    this.client.interceptors.request.use((config) => {
      const token = authStore.getState().accessToken;
      if (token) config.headers.Authorization = `Bearer ${token}`;
      return config;
    });

    // Response interceptor: Handle 401, 403, rate limiting
    this.client.interceptors.response.use(
      (response) => response,
      (error) => {
        if (error.response?.status === 401) {
          authStore.getState().logout();
          window.location.href = '/login';
        }
        return Promise.reject(error);
      }
    );
  }
}

React Query Integration Pattern
typescript
// features/manager/hooks/useTeamData.ts
export const useTeamData = (cycleId: string) => {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['team', cycleId],
    queryFn: () => teamService.getTeamMembers(cycleId),
    staleTime: 5 * 60 * 1000,  // 5 minutes
    refetchOnWindowFocus: false
  });
};

// Mutation for updating appraisal draft
export const useUpdateAppraisalDraft = () => {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();

  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: (data: UpdateDraftPayload) => appraisalService.updateDraft(data),
    onSuccess: (data, variables) => {
      // Invalidate and refetch
      queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['appraisal', variables.employeeId] });
      // Show success toast
      notificationStore.getState().showSuccess('Draft saved');
    },
    onError: (error) => {
      notificationStore.getState().showError('Failed to save draft');
    }
  });
};
6. Error and Loading Handling
Loading States
Pattern	Component	Use Case
Skeleton Screens	<DataTableSkeleton />	Initial page load for dashboards
Spinner Overlay	<FullPageSpinner />	Form submission, critical actions
Inline Skeleton	<MetricCardSkeleton />	Individual card loading
Progressive Loading	React Query isFetching	Background refetch (show subtle indicator)
tsx
// Example: Dashboard with loading states
const DashboardPage = () => {
  const { data, isLoading, isFetching, error } = useDashboardData();

  if (isLoading) return <DashboardSkeleton />;
  if (error) return <ErrorFallback error={error} retry={refetch} />;

  return (
    <div>
      {isFetching && <TopProgressBar />}  {/* Subtle indicator for background refetch */}
      <PerformanceChart data={data} />
    </div>
  );
};
Error Handling Patterns
Error Type	User Experience	Recovery
Network Error	Banner: "Connection lost. Retrying..."	Auto-retry with exponential backoff (3 attempts)
403 Forbidden	Modal: "You don't have permission to view this"	Redirect to role-appropriate dashboard
404 Not Found	Page: "Appraisal not found" + link to dashboard	Manual navigation
Validation Error	Inline form errors (Zod + React Hook Form)	User correction + resubmit
Server 500	Toast + error tracking to Sentry	Retry button or contact support
Rate Limit (429)	"Too many requests. Waiting 5 seconds..."	Automatic retry with delay
Global Error Boundary
tsx
// components/common/ErrorBoundary.tsx
class AppErrorBoundary extends React.Component {
  componentDidCatch(error: Error, errorInfo: React.ErrorInfo) {
    // Log to monitoring service (Sentry/DataDog)
    logger.error('Uncaught error:', { error, errorInfo });
  }

  render() {
    if (this.state.hasError) {
      return (
        <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center h-screen">
          <h1>Something went wrong</h1>
          <Button onClick={() => window.location.reload()}>Refresh Page</Button>
          <Button variant="ghost" onClick={() => navigate('/')}>Go Home</Button>
        </div>
      );
    }
    return this.props.children;
  }
}
7. Reusability Principles
Principle 1: Composition over Configuration
Bad: <DataTable columns=[...] rows=[...] customRender={...} /> (massive prop drilling)

Good: Compose features using slots

tsx
<DataTable>
  <DataTable.Header>
    <DataTable.Column field="name">Name</DataTable.Column>
  </DataTable.Header>
  <DataTable.Body>
    {items.map(item => <DataTableRow item={item} />)}
  </DataTable.Body>
</DataTable>
Principle 2: Custom Hooks for Business Logic
Components should be presentation-only

All API calls, transformations, and state go into hooks/

Principle 3: Atomic Design for UI Components
Atoms: Button, Input, Badge (shadcn/ui base)

Molecules: SearchBar, MetricCard, AlertBanner

Organisms: TeamMemberList, CalibrationIssuesTable

Templates: DashboardLayout, FormLayout

Pages: Route-specific composition

Principle 4: Type-First Development
API response types generated from OpenAPI spec (if available)

Shared types between frontend and backend via types/ directory

Strict TypeScript: noImplicitAny, strictNullChecks

Principle 5: Feature-Based Colocation
text
features/manager/
├── components/     # Only used by manager feature
├── hooks/          # Only used by manager feature
├── types/          # Feature-specific types
└── utils/          # Feature-specific helpers
Principle 6: Performance Optimization Rules
React.memo() for expensive list items (TeamMemberRow)

useCallback for functions passed to child components

useMemo for derived data (filtered/sorted lists)

Virtual scrolling for lists > 100 items (react-window)

Lazy loading for route-level code splitting:

tsx
const HRDashboard = lazy(() => import('./pages/HRDashboardPage'));
8. Real-time Updates (WebSocket)
For live sync notifications (data source updates, AI draft completion):

typescript
// hooks/useWebSocket.ts
export const useAppraisalUpdates = (employeeId: string) => {
  useEffect(() => {
    const ws = new WebSocket(`${WS_URL}/appraisals/${employeeId}`);
    ws.onmessage = (event) => {
      const update = JSON.parse(event.data);
      queryClient.setQueryData(['appraisal', employeeId], update.data);
      notificationStore.getState().showInfo('New data synced');
    };
    return () => ws.close();
  }, [employeeId]);
};

WS_URL (WebSocket URL) is the endpoint address used to establish a real-time, bidirectional WebSocket connection between the frontend client and the backend server.

In the context of the AI-Powered Appraisal System described in the frontend design document, WS_URL would be used for live updates such as:

Purpose in the Appraisal System
Use Case	Real-time Update Example
Data sync completion	"Jira data just synced - 247 new tickets processed"
AI draft generation	"Sarah Chen's AI appraisal draft is ready to review"
Metric changes	"New commit detected from Marcus"
Manager overrides	"Manager just adjusted rating for Priya Patel"
Calibration alerts	"New bias pattern detected in John Smith's team"
Employee context submission	"Sarah added context about her April metrics"
